England Leads India by 486 After Alastair Cook Scores Career High of 294

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-08-12T17:00:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/england-leads-india-by-486-after-alastair-cook-scores-career-high-of-294.html
Alastair Cook  scored a career-high
294 to lead England to 710-7 declared aganst  India , its highest
score in a cricket Test match in 73 years.  Cook’s total was the most by an English batsman since
Graham Gooch’s 333 against India in 1990. England’s total was
its third highest of all-time and its most since scoring 903-7
declared against Australia in 1938. India was bowled out for 224
in its first innings at Edgbaston in Birmingham.  England won the first two Tests in the four-match series.
It can replace India as No. 1 in the International Cricket
Council rankings with another victory or by drawing the final
two matches.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  